LOCALITY: Goleta Beach County Park (including east end of Goleta Slough)

TRIP COMMENTS: Other observers: Dave Compton, Grant Weyburne, Alison Kent, Allan Hollander, Pat McNulty, Claus Holzapfel. Bill Murdoch joined us for a short period.--Intent:  To continue our observations of Area K’s support for birds in this year when water retention is prolonged.  --Coverage and conditions: We stood the entire time at various points on the bluff to the S of Area K, which is immediately N of the UCSB Environmental Health and Safety facility.  This impounded wetland is entirely inundated but beginning to expose mudflats along N edge.  Thus, conditions are perfect for a broad range of shorebird preferences.  Some of the numbers involve best estimates by the entire group. Species with ‘0” are ones seen recently at this site but not today.--Original notes reside at the UCSB Center for Biodiversity and Ecological Restoration Field Note Archive: Goleta Slough Area K 13 Sept 98.pdf
